A difference in the 'starting point' of a workflow is possible, using a similar cycle or subset of the cycle of another workflow.
A workflow can instead start at this point of 'differences (errors)
from functions/solution metrics' and apply "all" and "opposite direction" to generate another workflow: "identify all solution metrics that are useful and changes to them that create solutions in specific problem spaces"
"Differences between all useful combinations of solution metrics and function types" is another useful structure to compute (as opposed to computing "combinations of solution components" and "differences from combined solution components and a specific set of solution metrics"), which applies a reverse direction of "identifying/applying useful changes like specifications of solution metrics to solution metrics to connect solution metrics to problems" rather than "identifying/applying useful changes to problems to connect to solution metrics" and "identifying all optimal/solution structures or identifying the variables of all solution structures" instead of "identifying a specific solution to a specific problem"
